{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease 2 small loaf tins (18 x 8 cm), then line a large baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites into mixing bowl and whip <b>5 min\/37°C\/speed 3.5<b>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>, until soft peaks form.","With butterfly whisk still in place, whip <b>3 min\/37°C\/speed 3.5<b>, slowly adding sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Add flour, almonds and chocolate chips (optional) and combine <b>10 sec\/\/speed 1.5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then combine for a further <b>20 sec\/\/speed 1.5<b>, or until completely combined.","Divide mixture evenly between the 2 prepared loaf tins and smooth over the tops using a dampened pastry brush. Bake for 25-35 minutes (180°C) or until lightly golden and a wooden skewer inserted into the centre of the loaves comes out clean.","Remove biscotti from oven and cut while still hot into thin slices (3mm) using a serrated bread knife. Place slices onto prepared baking tray, then bake slices for a further 5 minutes (180°C) or until just crispy.","Set biscotti aside to cool (approx. 20 minutes), then serve or place into a gift bag to give to friends and family."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["butter, for greasing","3 egg whites, room temperature","170 g caster sugar","200 g plain flour","130 g raw almonds","40 g dark chocolate chips              (optional)"]}],"id":"r90145","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-BXfys7sGetw\/XZWqx8fWTII\/AAAAAAAAfdQ\/JeLHrwrHr08lPZKRD0-W16vtvtTPeNnNQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_UUA1P_jcIQ2INTRo.png","title":"Almond biscotti","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"1.3 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"5 g","calories":"151 kJ \/ 36 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, 2 small loaf tins (18 x 8 cm), wooden skewer, pastry brush, serrated bread knife, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Serve biscotti with your cup of coffee, tea or hot chocolate as a special treat.","If you are giving biscotti as a gift, include a bag of freshly ground coffee beans to complete the gift and create a mini-hamper any coffee drinker would love. Place 150 g coffee beans into mixing bowl and grind <strong>10-30 sec\/speed 9<\/strong>. For a coarser grind (ideal for plunger coffee) grind for 10 seconds or for a finer grind (ideal for espresso\/coffee machines), grind for 30 seconds."],"basicInfo":["medium","10m","1h 10m","67 pieces"]}